  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Junior Investment Analyst",
  "description": "<p>Broad Peak is looking for a junior investment analyst to support its investment process focused on investing in publicly traded equities and debt instruments in the Pan Asia region. This is a graduate hire role and is not open to those with prior employment or anyone who has graduated for more than twelve months.\n </p><p><strong>What Will You Learn & Do In The Role</strong></p><p>In this role, you will be required to support Broad Peak’s senior investment analysts in:</p><ul><li>developing and maintaining financial models, performing investment due diligence and generally helping in tasks needing to be performed as part of the investment process;  </li><li>undertaking industry research and financial analysis;</li><li>monitoring news and other events related to investments in the portfolio; and</li><li>helping develop tools and executing on projects that will help improve the overall investment process.</li></ul><p><strong>What Attributes Should You Have</strong></p><p>You should be able to demonstrate the following attributes:</p><ul><li>rigorous research skills and good attention to detail;</li><li>excellent numerical skills and the ability to apply them;</li><li>proficiency in excel and the ability to build foundational financial models;</li><li>proficiency in using Bloomberg with the knowledge of how to extract financial information into spreadsheets and other destinations; </li><li>a keen interest in current affairs;</li><li>the ability to work effectively under pressure and within tight time constraints;</li><li>an inquisitive and analytical mind with the ability to problem-solve;</li><li>a good communicator and a team player who is able to listen to and take instructions effectively; and</li><li>having a genuine interest in investing (and possibly having done some personal investing already).</li></ul>",
